:HELP     NAME='cwdh'.
Local Directory Listing - Help
:XH3.Local Directory Listing
:P.
Use this panel view the contents of the Current Working Directory
which is changed using various methods.
The content of the directory is complete with a full list of the
objects within the directory. Care should be taken when dealing with
QSYS.LIB directory and its sub directories. The request to display the
QSYS.LIB directory could take many minutes to complete due to the
number of objects which exist within that directory. The maximum list
storage can be exceeded when viewing this directory which will result
in a program failure.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME='lclopth'.
Directory Options - Help
:XH3.Directory Options
:P.The following options are available from this panel.
:XH3.Options Available :
:PARML.
:PT.1 Put/Get File
:PD.
:P.This will result in the object selected being transfered to the
appropriatesystem. If the selected object is a directory, the directory
and all of its contents will be transfered to the appropriate system.
Ensure that the appropriate Current Working Directory is correctly set
before making the request. The transfer mode can affect the useability
of the object after a transfer.
:PT.2 Edit
:PD.
:P.This will invoke the editor EDTF against the selected object. This option
is only availble when the local Current Woring Directory is displayed.
:PT.5 View
:PD.
:P.This will change the Current Working Directory or display the object contents
if the object is a *STMF. If you select the '..' entry the higher level
directory will be shown. If the selected object is from the target system it
will be transfered to the local system before being displayed. After closing the
display the temporary object will be destroyed.
:PT.4 Delete
:PD.
:P. This will delete the selected object. If the object is a directory
all lower level directories and objects will also be deleted.
:PT.7 Rename
:PD.
:P.This allows you to rename a file, directory or library.
:PT.8 Display Detail
:PD.
:P.This will show the detail of the object selected. The size of the
object is shown in TB(TerraByte),GB(GigaByte),MB(MegaByte),kB(KiloByte)
or B(Byte) rounded to the nearest decimal position.
:EPARML.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=putfh.
Put File- Help
:XH3.Put File
:P.
Option to Put a file to the remote system. The file will be copied to
the Remote system and placed in the Current Working Directory on that
system. To check the current working directory on the remote system use
F8 Display Remote Directory from the Site List Panel.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=getfh.
Get File- Help
:XH3.Get File
:P.
Option to get a file from the remote system. The file will be copied to
the Local system and placed in the Current Working Directory on that
system. To check the current working directory on the local system use
F8 Display Remote Directory Key.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=edtfh.
Edit File- Help
:XH3.Edit File
:P.
Option to Edit a file on the local system. The EDTF command will be
run against the selected object.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=nxtlvlh.
View - Help
:XH3.View Directory or object
:P.
Option to change the Current Working Directory or view object. The list will
be refreshed and the Current Working Directory Variable updated if the object
is a *DIR object, if the object selected is the '..' entry the higher level
directory will be shown. An error message is sent if you attempt to go beyond
the root directory. If the object selected is a *STMF its contents will be
displayed, also if the object is from the remote system a local temporary
copy will be created before the display is created.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=dltfh.
Delete - Help
:XH3.Delete
:P.
Option to delete the selected object. If the object is a directory the
lower level directories and objects will also be deleted automatically.
:EHELP.
