.*------------------------------------------------------------------
.*  Site List Panel
.*------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP     NAME='sitelh'.
Site List - Help
:XH3.Site List
:P.
This panel gives a list of the sites which have been configured by
a user.  The list is stored for retrieval later and contains the basic
information required to connect to a Remote FTP Server.
Options are provided to add and remove as well as change site
information.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=useridh.
User - Help
:XH3.User
:P.
The User who is signed onto this session.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME='cnnopth'.
Site List Options - Help
:XH3.Site List Options
:P.The following options are available from this panel.
:XH3.Options Available :
:PARML.
:PT.1 Connect
:PD.
:P.This options will use the information provided to connect to the
remote FTP Server. Messages are sent to the log if any errors occur.
Once connected the list of options available and the Function Keys
available will be changed.
:PT.2 Change Entry
:PD.
:P.This option is only available when Not Connected Status is shown.
Using this option you can change the parameters used to connect to
the remote FTP Server.
:PT.3 Disconnect
:PD.
:P.This option is only available when the system is connected to the
remote FTP Server. This option will close the connection and close
the ports opened during the session.
:PT.4 Delete Entry
:PD.
:P. This will delete the selected entry.
:EPARML.
:EHELP.
.*
.*------------------------------------------------------------------
.*  Change Site Details Panel
.*------------------------------------------------------------------
:HELP     NAME='SITEDET/'.
Site Detail - Help
:XH3.Site Detail
:P.
This panel allows the entering of the information required to make a
connection to a Remote FTP Server. The password entered will be
encrypted before being stored in the database. If the remote path
does not exist the default path will be used. The remote address can
be in either dotted decimal '192.168.100.111' or english 'Helios' the
address must be available for translation in either the local hosts
or by the use of a DNS server. When entering the retry values, remember
that the delay will be used as both a timer for the connection attempt
and as a delay between attempts.  The standard timeout for a connect()
is 75 seconds, if the delay is set to more than this number the
connect() will still return after 75 secs but the delay between
attempts will be the number of seconds entered.
The retry value is the number of retries to ba taken, therefore if it
is set to 1, two attempts to connect will be made.
QSYS.LIB will take a long time to load on the local system due to the
high number of objects and the processing required to extract the
information about each object, it is therefore advisable not to use
/QSYS.LIB as the starting point for a system connection.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=sitelblh.
Site Label - Help
:XH3.Site Label
:P.
This is a unique name assigned to this site. If does not have to
relate to the address of the system and can be a string of words
such as 'Unix System in Head Office'.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=hostadrh.
Host Address - Help
:XH3.Host Address
:P.
A valid host address for the remote system. It can either be in dotted
decimal format ie: '192.168.100.111' or english ie:'Helios'. The
address must be resolvable by either a host file or a DNS server if
entered in english format. The route to the remote server must be
reachable from your network.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=rmtporth.
Remote Port - Help
:XH3.Remote Port
:P.
The port used by the remote FTP server. Port 21 is the default and
should be used unless you are running a non standard FTP server.
SSL connections are not supported in this release.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=pwdh.
Password - Help
:XH3.Password
:P.
The password to be sent to the remote system. The password is
encrypted before being stored and decrypted prior to being sent to
the remote server automatically. All normal FTP Servers require the
Password to be sent in plain text format.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=rmtdirh.
Remote Directory - Help
:XH3.Remote Directory
:P.
The directory which is to become the initial Current Working
Directory on the remote system. Any transfers between the two systems
will be made between the Current Working Directories. Every time you
change directory on each system the Current Working Directory will be
set automatically for you.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=lcldirh.
Local Directory - Help
:XH3.Local Directory
:P.
The directory which is to become the initial Current Working
Directory on the local system. Any transfers between the two systems
will be made between the Current Working Directories. Every time you
change directory on each system the Current Working Directory will be
set automatically for you.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=cnnrtyh.
Connection Retry - Help
:XH3.Connection Retry
:P.
The number of times the program will attempt to connect to the remote
system after the initial attempt fails. This parameter is only used on
the connect() function.
:EHELP.
.*
:HELP     NAME=cnndlyh.
Connection Delay - Help
:XH3.Connection Delay
:P.
The number of seconds the connect() function will wait for a response
from the remote system, also the length of time in seconds the process
will wait between each rety. The connect() function normally returns
after 75 seconds of processing time if a response has not been received
from the remote system. Therefore setting this number higher than 75
will have no effect on the connect() function. This value is also used
to determine the delay between the connect() requests, if you enter a
number higher than 75, the program will continue to delay for the
number of seconds entered.
:EHELP.
